1
00:00:13,540 --> 00:00:15,780
♪Trap my frame♪

2
00:00:15,980 --> 00:00:20,060
♪Plagues demand I bow in shame♪

3
00:00:20,780 --> 00:00:22,940
♪Snare my soul♪

4
00:00:23,020 --> 00:00:27,100
♪Rules command I swallow my pride♪

5
00:00:27,260 --> 00:00:30,620
♪Mock my way♪

6
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:34,060
♪Chained me where I must stay♪

7
00:00:34,420 --> 00:00:36,780
♪Taught me to kneel, not to speak♪

8
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:41,220
♪And to let my life pass by in silence♪

9
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:44,100
♪But I heard the wind♪

10
00:00:44,220 --> 00:00:45,900
♪From the sea and the sky♪

11
00:00:46,180 --> 00:00:47,660
♪It said don't bend♪

12
00:00:47,780 --> 00:00:49,820
♪Bow your head, and your chains begin♪

13
00:00:49,940 --> 00:00:51,380
♪You are the wave♪

14
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:53,300
♪And the wind that won't behave♪

15
00:00:53,380 --> 00:00:56,340
♪How could you be chained?♪

16
00:00:56,740 --> 00:00:58,740
♪Untamed, uncaged, unclaimed♪

17
00:00:58,780 --> 00:01:00,540
♪You're the blade in my gaze♪

18
00:01:00,620 --> 00:01:02,420
♪This world will leave you no space♪

19
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:04,220
♪Then pierce it with your blaze♪

20
00:01:04,220 --> 00:01:06,100
♪My silent grind♪

21
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:08,060
♪My aching pain♪

22
00:01:08,060 --> 00:01:10,300
♪Will one day turn...♪

23
00:01:11,860 --> 00:01:14,620
♪I am who I am♪

24
00:01:14,620 --> 00:01:18,140
♪My greatest ambition♪

25
00:01:18,220 --> 00:01:21,300
♪If the world can't contain me♪

26
00:01:21,380 --> 00:01:24,940
♪Then I'll break through it♪

27
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:26,940
♪Become who I am♪

28
00:01:26,940 --> 00:01:28,260
[Wild Ambition Bloom]

29
00:01:28,260 --> 00:01:29,980
[Adapted from Stone and Water's novel,
The Uncaged Flame]

30
00:01:29,980 --> 00:01:32,980
[Episode 14]

31
00:01:58,640 --> 00:02:03,700
♪Draped in the long night's bitter snow♪

32
00:02:04,380 --> 00:02:11,980
♪Where lies the final destination?
Looking up, is it heaven or the abyss?♪

33
00:02:12,460 --> 00:02:15,860
♪The night watchman
with his lamp is gone♪

34
00:02:16,420 --> 00:02:22,740
♪The light I followed
was but a firefly's deceit♪

35
00:02:23,020 --> 00:02:28,940
♪Who judges right from wrong,
and who breaks the judge's gavel?♪

36
00:02:29,340 --> 00:02:36,420
♪If faith collapses,
where do answers lie?♪

37
00:02:37,820 --> 00:02:43,540
♪Black and white entwined,
day and night reversed♪

38
00:02:43,980 --> 00:02:49,620
♪The flame within my heart
can only blaze when fed with tears♪

39
00:02:50,060 --> 00:02:52,310
♪Heaven and Earth shatter,
awaiting fire's final breach♪

40
00:02:52,310 --> 00:02:54,610
Mother, I can sing English songs now!

41
00:02:55,030 --> 00:02:57,010
Mother, don't tire yourself out.

42
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:58,730
Mommy, I love you.

43
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:00,820
Don't bully my mother!

44
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:02,220
Xuan!

45
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:03,820
Stop crying!

46
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:06,610
Let's take her to France!

47
00:03:07,030 --> 00:03:07,890
Expose her early

48
00:03:07,910 --> 00:03:09,100
to cutting-edge science,

49
00:03:09,310 --> 00:03:10,570
immerse her in diverse cultures,

50
00:03:10,910 --> 00:03:12,290
and let her experience
the vastness of the world!

51
00:03:14,860 --> 00:03:20,140
♪Through cages woven with broken towers♪

52
00:03:20,620 --> 00:03:25,580
♪How many eyes of greed
lurk in the shade?♪

53
00:03:25,590 --> 00:03:27,340
Mr. Xia, we should get going.

54
00:03:29,180 --> 00:03:32,340
♪Draining the sun's last glow♪

55
00:03:32,780 --> 00:03:38,460
♪On crumbled peaks,
will dawn break anew?♪

56
00:03:38,780 --> 00:03:45,380
♪How to discern its shadow
when my eyes are blindfolded?♪

57
00:03:45,660 --> 00:03:50,900
♪If longing for the light,
you can endure the cold night♪

58
00:03:51,380 --> 00:03:56,940
♪Black and white entwined,
day and night reversed♪

59
00:03:57,380 --> 00:04:03,020
♪The flame within my heart
can only blaze when fed with tears♪

60
00:04:03,460 --> 00:04:08,980
♪Heaven and Earth shatter,
awaiting fire's final breach♪

61
00:04:09,420 --> 00:04:15,900
♪Dust of the night
shields the future from decay♪

62
00:04:15,910 --> 00:04:16,780
Sorry.

63
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:26,220
Hey,

64
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:27,900
where are you going?

65
00:04:32,830 --> 00:04:34,490
I'm going to see my cousin.

66
00:04:36,380 --> 00:04:37,250
I want to go to Shanghai.

67
00:04:38,580 --> 00:04:39,700
Me too.

68
00:04:41,900 --> 00:04:44,740
[Shanghai]

69
00:04:56,460 --> 00:04:57,820
So this is Shanghai.

70
00:04:59,180 --> 00:05:00,020
It's so lively.

71
00:05:05,020 --> 00:05:06,140
Extra!

72
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:08,540
Extra!

73
00:05:18,140 --> 00:05:18,660
Hey,

74
00:05:18,940 --> 00:05:20,540
if you don't have anywhere to go,

75
00:05:20,660 --> 00:05:22,380
you can come with me to the cotton mill.

76
00:05:22,940 --> 00:05:23,740
What cotton mill?

77
00:05:25,060 --> 00:05:27,380
Baoxing Cotton Mill on Yangshupu Road.

78
00:05:28,060 --> 00:05:29,580
My cousin works there.

79
00:05:29,860 --> 00:05:31,380
She said if you do well,

80
00:05:31,740 --> 00:05:33,260
you can earn over ten dollars a month.

81
00:05:33,420 --> 00:05:35,260
Even if you're new and not that good,

82
00:05:35,260 --> 00:05:36,740
you can still make four or five dollars.

83
00:05:39,660 --> 00:05:42,140
But I need to find my sister first.

84
00:05:43,660 --> 00:05:44,700
Alright then.

85
00:05:45,980 --> 00:05:46,620
Thanks.

86
00:05:47,740 --> 00:05:48,340
Goodbye.

87
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:00,300
Hey,

88
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:03,060
once you've settled in,

89
00:06:03,620 --> 00:06:04,620
come find me if you feel like it.

90
00:06:26,220 --> 00:06:27,060
Number 89.

91
00:06:27,060 --> 00:06:28,420
Your letter. It's from Shanghai.

92
00:06:29,220 --> 00:06:30,900
[To Chu Shaohua]
That must be from Erniu.

93
00:06:31,580 --> 00:06:32,420
Number 89.

94
00:06:32,860 --> 00:06:33,540
Erniu.

95
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:39,820
Erniu.

96
00:06:42,340 --> 00:06:43,340
Who are you looking for?

97
00:06:43,820 --> 00:06:46,020
I'm here to see Kang Erniu.

98
00:06:47,180 --> 00:06:48,540
You've got the wrong place.

99
00:06:48,900 --> 00:06:50,700
There's no such person.

100
00:06:54,300 --> 00:06:55,540
My sister

101
00:06:55,820 --> 00:06:57,180
wrote to me before.

102
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:58,940
The address she gave me

103
00:06:59,220 --> 00:07:00,660
was Number 89.

104
00:07:01,300 --> 00:07:03,060
She said she was working here as a maid.

105
00:07:03,420 --> 00:07:04,540
Her name is Kang Erniu.

106
00:07:05,900 --> 00:07:07,940
When did this happen?

107
00:07:09,780 --> 00:07:10,580
Sorry,

108
00:07:10,740 --> 00:07:12,900
but I really don't understand
what you're talking about.

109
00:07:13,340 --> 00:07:14,380
I'm asking you

110
00:07:14,380 --> 00:07:16,260
when this happened.

111
00:07:18,540 --> 00:07:19,420
Four years ago.

112
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:23,820
I just moved here last year.

113
00:07:23,860 --> 00:07:25,820
Just...what?

114
00:07:25,940 --> 00:07:27,540
I just moved here.

115
00:07:28,260 --> 00:07:29,380
What about the people
who lived here before?

116
00:07:29,380 --> 00:07:30,580
Do you know

117
00:07:30,580 --> 00:07:31,420
where they moved to?

118
00:07:33,660 --> 00:07:34,300
No idea.

119
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:32,600
[Xu Shengchang Inn]

120
00:08:39,670 --> 00:08:42,670
[Fifty Wen Per Night]

121
00:09:21,380 --> 00:09:25,020
Today, the capitalists were forced
to negotiate with the workers.

122
00:09:25,340 --> 00:09:27,260
They signed four agreements,

123
00:09:27,260 --> 00:09:28,660
including a ban on unjust dismissal.

124
00:09:29,140 --> 00:09:29,740
As of now,

125
00:09:30,060 --> 00:09:32,180
the strikes at the First, Second,

126
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:33,860
and Third Cotton Mills

127
00:09:33,980 --> 00:09:35,220
have ended in victory.

128
00:09:35,980 --> 00:09:37,940
That concludes today's news broadcast.

129
00:09:38,260 --> 00:09:42,740
Up next, Suzhou Pingtan performance,
"Entrusting Three Matters."

130
00:09:43,900 --> 00:09:44,460
Sir.

131
00:09:45,380 --> 00:09:46,940
[Yangchun Noodles]
Mr. Wen, what can I get you today?

132
00:09:47,180 --> 00:09:47,860
Same as usual.

133
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:48,860
Got it.

134
00:10:12,980 --> 00:10:14,180
[Recruitment Spot]
The cotton mill is hiring!

135
00:10:14,180 --> 00:10:14,740
Age?

136
00:10:14,740 --> 00:10:15,380
I'm twenty-two.

137
00:10:15,380 --> 00:10:16,660
You came at just the right time.

138
00:10:16,660 --> 00:10:18,300
The factory's hiring a lot these days.

139
00:10:18,300 --> 00:10:19,660
I started work just yesterday.

140
00:10:19,780 --> 00:10:21,260
We don't take anyone over 40!

141
00:10:21,380 --> 00:10:22,660
If they ask you anything,
don't say a word.

142
00:10:22,860 --> 00:10:23,700
Just follow my lead.

143
00:10:24,540 --> 00:10:26,380
Line up!

144
00:10:26,380 --> 00:10:26,900
Next.

145
00:10:26,900 --> 00:10:28,180
Get in line.

146
00:10:28,260 --> 00:10:28,820
Zhong.

147
00:10:30,380 --> 00:10:31,100
Mr. Huang.

148
00:10:31,300 --> 00:10:32,460
You think we'll get enough
coming in today?

149
00:10:34,020 --> 00:10:34,980
Pretty much.

150
00:10:35,940 --> 00:10:36,900
What do you mean, "pretty much"?

151
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:37,620
OK. Next.

152
00:10:37,620 --> 00:10:38,380
Listen.

153
00:10:38,740 --> 00:10:40,060
If we're short on people

154
00:10:40,060 --> 00:10:41,500
and that batch of British goods
doesn't get finished,

155
00:10:41,620 --> 00:10:42,660
and the boss ends up losing money,

156
00:10:43,100 --> 00:10:44,580
we'll both be in deep trouble.

157
00:10:45,060 --> 00:10:45,740
Don't worry.

158
00:10:45,740 --> 00:10:46,180
Next.

159
00:10:46,180 --> 00:10:47,060
I've got this.

160
00:10:47,740 --> 00:10:48,500
Hurry up.

161
00:10:49,140 --> 00:10:50,620
Come on. Line up.

162
00:10:50,620 --> 00:10:51,380
Got any work experience?

163
00:10:51,380 --> 00:10:51,980
Move up.

164
00:10:51,980 --> 00:10:52,660
No.

165
00:10:53,780 --> 00:10:54,420
Twenty-four.

166
00:10:54,420 --> 00:10:57,180
Our cotton mill is hiring.
Limited spots!

167
00:10:57,580 --> 00:10:58,380
Hurry up and get in line!

168
00:10:58,380 --> 00:10:58,980
Next!

169
00:10:59,010 --> 00:10:59,820
[Shanghai Baoxing Cotton Mill]

170
00:10:59,820 --> 00:11:00,460
Name.

171
00:11:00,780 --> 00:11:01,900
Chen Xiaolan, 33.

172
00:11:02,620 --> 00:11:03,500
Got any work experience?

173
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:04,100
Yes.

174
00:11:05,020 --> 00:11:06,140
Everyone, come on over!

175
00:11:06,340 --> 00:11:08,540
Good pay, great meals!

176
00:11:08,540 --> 00:11:09,300
Hurry up!

177
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:10,140
Got any work experience?

178
00:11:10,140 --> 00:11:10,540
Yes.

179
00:11:10,860 --> 00:11:11,540
Next!

180
00:11:13,220 --> 00:11:14,980
Could you help register my friend?

181
00:11:14,980 --> 00:11:16,020
Alright, name.

182
00:11:18,980 --> 00:11:19,620
What's your name?

183
00:11:19,940 --> 00:11:20,700
Zhu Sha.

184
00:11:21,420 --> 00:11:22,020
Age?

185
00:11:22,820 --> 00:11:23,540
Eighteen.

186
00:11:25,660 --> 00:11:26,340
Guarantor?

187
00:11:27,260 --> 00:11:28,700
Luo Cuiying,
from the drawing frame workshop.

188
00:11:30,620 --> 00:11:31,620
Got any work experience?

189
00:11:32,220 --> 00:11:32,780
Yes.

190
00:11:32,780 --> 00:11:34,660
She worked at a cotton mill in Qingdao,

191
00:11:34,780 --> 00:11:35,580
same section.

192
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:38,820
Then head straight there.

193
00:11:39,580 --> 00:11:41,140
Alright, thank you.

194
00:11:41,140 --> 00:11:41,700
Next.

195
00:11:41,700 --> 00:11:42,100
Thanks.

196
00:11:42,620 --> 00:11:43,220
Thanks.

197
00:11:43,660 --> 00:11:44,500
That's it?

198
00:11:44,860 --> 00:11:45,380
Over there.

199
00:11:45,380 --> 00:11:45,900
Cuiying,

200
00:11:46,180 --> 00:11:47,300
I'm not 18.

201
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:48,660
I know.

202
00:11:49,140 --> 00:11:50,580
But older and younger ones

203
00:11:50,580 --> 00:11:52,380
get sent to the raw silk workshop
to reel cocoons

204
00:11:52,660 --> 00:11:53,860
and stand all day long.

205
00:11:53,860 --> 00:11:54,860
It's the hardest job.

206
00:11:54,860 --> 00:11:57,260
But I've never worked
at the cotton mill in Qingdao.

207
00:11:57,940 --> 00:11:58,780
I know.

208
00:11:59,340 --> 00:12:01,180
But skilled workers can start right away

209
00:12:01,780 --> 00:12:03,140
and earn a bit more too.

210
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:05,580
But I don't know
how to do drawing frame work.

211
00:12:06,660 --> 00:12:08,220
It's okay. I'll teach you.

212
00:12:09,980 --> 00:12:11,140
Thank you, Cuiying.

213
00:12:11,340 --> 00:12:11,900
Let's go.

214
00:12:12,060 --> 00:12:12,620
Come on.

215
00:12:16,060 --> 00:12:16,940
Hurry up!

216
00:12:17,300 --> 00:12:18,340
Stop dawdling.

217
00:12:18,740 --> 00:12:19,540
Keep up.

218
00:12:20,500 --> 00:12:22,580
That clock runs our lives.

219
00:12:22,780 --> 00:12:24,780
Once the hand reaches here,
we start work.

220
00:12:25,300 --> 00:12:27,300
Only when it makes a full circle
can we stop.

221
00:12:27,740 --> 00:12:29,260
Take a tag if you need
to use the restroom.

222
00:12:29,740 --> 00:12:31,580
If you're gone too long,
you'll get beaten.

223
00:12:32,780 --> 00:12:34,540
The three of us
will be working on this machine.

224
00:12:35,220 --> 00:12:36,300
It's not hard.

225
00:12:36,420 --> 00:12:38,180
You just need to be careful
and quick with your hands.

226
00:12:38,620 --> 00:12:39,300
Like this,

227
00:12:40,100 --> 00:12:42,420
combine several slivers of cotton.

228
00:12:42,420 --> 00:12:44,820
The merged sliver
should be even in weight.

229
00:12:44,820 --> 00:12:45,260
OK.

230
00:12:45,620 --> 00:12:47,580
And the fibers should be neatly aligned.

231
00:12:56,940 --> 00:12:57,580
Oh, right.

232
00:12:57,740 --> 00:13:00,700
It's better to go slow
than make mistakes.

233
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:02,730
If you're slow, you might get hit.

234
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:04,250
But if you mess up,

235
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:05,250
you'll get hit,

236
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:06,490
and they'll dock your pay.

237
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:11,100
Do people here get hit and fined a lot?

238
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:13,490
You'll get used to it.

239
00:13:14,550 --> 00:13:15,250
You three.

240
00:13:15,790 --> 00:13:16,850
What are you chatting about?

241
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:18,770
Want me to come down
and join the conversation?

242
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:19,890
Let's get back to work.

243
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:21,060
Call me if you need help.

244
00:13:23,270 --> 00:13:23,940
Hurry up!

245
00:13:24,360 --> 00:13:25,370
Keep your hands moving.

246
00:13:26,150 --> 00:13:27,250
No dawdling!

247
00:13:59,150 --> 00:14:00,820
Spent ten minutes in the restroom?

248
00:14:02,270 --> 00:14:03,100
I'm sorry.

249
00:14:04,870 --> 00:14:05,730
Trying to slack off, huh?

250
00:14:07,120 --> 00:14:09,060
Please, have mercy.

251
00:14:09,790 --> 00:14:11,730
I'm on my period.

252
00:14:11,910 --> 00:14:13,890
My stomach hurts so bad.

253
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:17,130
I never slack off, I swear.

254
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:18,100
Get lost!

255
00:14:20,390 --> 00:14:21,100
What are you staring at?

256
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:23,300
Get back to work, now!

257
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:31,770
What I told you this morning

258
00:14:32,510 --> 00:14:33,300
applies to everyone.

259
00:14:34,510 --> 00:14:35,980
No one's getting special treatment.

260
00:14:37,030 --> 00:14:37,940
Hurry up and eat.

261
00:14:38,790 --> 00:14:40,010
So this is the meal

262
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:41,300
the factory provides?

263
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:44,100
You'll get used to it.

264
00:14:47,910 --> 00:14:48,530
Nothing.

265
00:15:03,030 --> 00:15:04,060
Food's pretty good today.

266
00:15:11,870 --> 00:15:12,610
Getting all shy now, are we?

267
00:15:15,860 --> 00:15:16,650
Don't look at them.

268
00:15:16,980 --> 00:15:17,610
Don't.

269
00:15:21,390 --> 00:15:22,530
You don't know Gui?

270
00:15:22,910 --> 00:15:23,580
She's new?

271
00:15:24,180 --> 00:15:24,890
Never seen her.

272
00:15:25,620 --> 00:15:26,530
Not bad.

273
00:15:26,960 --> 00:15:27,580
Yeah.

274
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:32,010
Such a tiny waist.

275
00:15:34,320 --> 00:15:34,890
Pretty,

276
00:15:36,030 --> 00:15:36,940
I'm Agui.

277
00:15:37,630 --> 00:15:40,220
I look after all the new arrivals.

278
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:44,130
I'll treat you
to something better next time.

279
00:15:46,080 --> 00:15:47,220
With skin like yours,

280
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:48,770
this factory grub's just unfair.

281
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:52,980
His old fling.

282
00:15:53,510 --> 00:15:54,250
Are we just letting that slide?

283
00:15:54,870 --> 00:15:56,100
They're with the Qing Gang.

284
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:57,610
We can't afford to mess with them.

285
00:15:58,720 --> 00:15:59,340
Gui,

286
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:00,250
your old fling.

287
00:16:10,390 --> 00:16:10,980
Go ahead.

288
00:16:11,670 --> 00:16:13,890
Zhu, you haven't finished your meal.

289
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:54,100
Doesn't feel as tiring as yesterday.

290
00:16:54,840 --> 00:16:56,220
You little brat, stop right there!

291
00:16:56,670 --> 00:16:57,850
You dare mess with my clock?

292
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,700
I swear I'll make you pay today!

293
00:17:00,440 --> 00:17:01,250
Stop right there!

294
00:17:04,510 --> 00:17:05,530
Stop!

295
00:17:06,030 --> 00:17:07,090
Don't run.

296
00:17:10,510 --> 00:17:11,810
Did you see a little brat run by?

297
00:17:11,880 --> 00:17:12,730
Yeah.

298
00:17:12,750 --> 00:17:14,090
He slammed into me. My back still hurts.

299
00:17:14,110 --> 00:17:14,940
Then he ran off.

300
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:15,620
Which way did he go?

301
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:16,330
That way.

302
00:17:17,590 --> 00:17:18,090
Let's go.

303
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:26,570
Come on.

304
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:30,220
Zhu's amazing.

305
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:35,120
[Shanghai Baoxing Cotton Mill]

306
00:17:36,870 --> 00:17:40,100
[Number 12]

307
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:45,980
The door's broken. It won't close.

308
00:17:48,030 --> 00:17:48,660
Zhu.

309
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:50,490
Come on.

310
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:51,730
You're late.

311
00:17:51,750 --> 00:17:52,660
Only the top bunk's left.

312
00:17:52,920 --> 00:17:53,730
You'll sleep here.

313
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:54,730
I'm right across from you.

314
00:17:55,550 --> 00:17:57,660
Cuiying, how long have you been here?

315
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:00,380
Two years.

316
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:04,530
You've lived like this the whole time?

317
00:18:06,110 --> 00:18:08,090
Better than sleeping
on the street, isn't it?

318
00:18:09,110 --> 00:18:11,220
The door's broken.

319
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:12,380
So were the windows.

320
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:14,010
How come no one fixed them?

321
00:18:15,350 --> 00:18:16,620
You'll get used to it.

322
00:18:18,270 --> 00:18:19,420
Why would I?

323
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:21,900
We can do something about this.

324
00:18:22,510 --> 00:18:23,380
Do what?

325
00:18:24,070 --> 00:18:25,570
When we just got here,

326
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:27,290
they told us

327
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:29,570
we'd work twelve hours a day.

328
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:31,900
But now we're working

329
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,860
way more than that.

330
00:18:34,160 --> 00:18:36,570
And they beat us, yell at us,
and dock our pay.

331
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:38,730
Even the male workers grope us.

332
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:41,810
Don't you think
something's wrong with this life?

333
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:44,530
That's just how life is.

334
00:18:44,720 --> 00:18:45,700
Everyone's going through the same thing.

335
00:18:45,920 --> 00:18:47,050
What's there to complain about?

336
00:18:49,310 --> 00:18:50,220
We're human, aren't we?

337
00:18:50,590 --> 00:18:51,660
Not animals.

338
00:18:51,920 --> 00:18:52,900
Even animals

339
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:54,940
get fed by their owners.

340
00:18:55,720 --> 00:18:57,460
Look at what we're eating.

341
00:18:58,510 --> 00:18:59,420
Even animals

342
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:00,810
get a roof

343
00:19:00,830 --> 00:19:02,730
over their heads.

344
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:04,530
Now look at where we sleep.

345
00:19:07,070 --> 00:19:08,660
Factories in Shanghai are all like this.

346
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:12,620
But just because they're all like this

347
00:19:12,640 --> 00:19:13,660
doesn't mean we have to accept it.

348
00:19:14,020 --> 00:19:14,860
But what other choice

349
00:19:15,260 --> 00:19:16,770
do we have?

350
00:19:16,830 --> 00:19:17,700
Of course we have one.

351
00:19:18,070 --> 00:19:20,010
We can stand together

352
00:19:20,260 --> 00:19:22,530
and negotiate
better conditions with the factory.

353
00:19:23,830 --> 00:19:25,090
What does that mean?

354
00:19:27,270 --> 00:19:28,250
It means

355
00:19:29,310 --> 00:19:32,010
we stick together,

356
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:34,420
like strands in a rope,

357
00:19:34,900 --> 00:19:35,980
thinking the same,

358
00:19:36,020 --> 00:19:37,180
pushing as one.

359
00:19:37,510 --> 00:19:40,570
Then you, I, and the rest of us

360
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:42,570
go and demand better treatment.

361
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:54,620
And then?

362
00:19:55,680 --> 00:19:57,090
Alright, it's getting late.

363
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:58,050
Everyone, get to sleep.

364
00:19:58,070 --> 00:19:59,180
We've got an early shift tomorrow.

365
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:00,330
That's enough. Come on. lights out.

366
00:20:21,460 --> 00:20:24,740
[One Month Later]

367
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:30,180
Easy.

368
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:30,940
Careful, Gui.

369
00:20:32,220 --> 00:20:32,780
Over there.

370
00:20:32,780 --> 00:20:33,860
- That way.
- Right there.

371
00:20:34,540 --> 00:20:35,260
That way.

372
00:20:38,260 --> 00:20:38,940
Over there!

373
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:44,380
Don't you dare bully my mother!

374
00:20:45,100 --> 00:20:46,340
Xuan, let go.

375
00:20:46,340 --> 00:20:47,460
I'm your uncle!

376
00:20:48,060 --> 00:20:48,860
Take your hands off!

377
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:50,940
Stop crying!

378
00:20:51,300 --> 00:20:52,020
Cut it out!

379
00:21:00,460 --> 00:21:02,860
Ladies, miss me?

380
00:21:11,460 --> 00:21:12,580
Cuiying.

381
00:21:12,900 --> 00:21:14,620
Stay back!

382
00:21:16,940 --> 00:21:17,860
Missed me?

383
00:21:17,860 --> 00:21:18,620
Don't come over!

384
00:21:18,620 --> 00:21:19,260
What are you doing?

385
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:20,260
What do you think you're doing?

386
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:22,060
Lian.

387
00:21:22,060 --> 00:21:22,700
Don't come over!

388
00:21:22,700 --> 00:21:24,460
Lian, here I come.

389
00:21:25,380 --> 00:21:25,940
Lian.

390
00:21:26,060 --> 00:21:27,740
Don't come any closer!

391
00:21:27,740 --> 00:21:28,460
Lian.

392
00:21:28,940 --> 00:21:29,980
Come on, just a little touch.

393
00:21:29,980 --> 00:21:30,740
Get away from me!

394
00:21:32,460 --> 00:21:33,300
Let go!

395
00:21:34,660 --> 00:21:35,260
Come on.

396
00:21:35,260 --> 00:21:36,140
I said get away!

397
00:21:36,140 --> 00:21:36,980
Be good, Lian.

398
00:21:36,980 --> 00:21:37,700
Let her go!

399
00:21:38,780 --> 00:21:39,580
Who's shouting?

400
00:21:40,700 --> 00:21:41,940
Slim Waist.

401
00:21:42,540 --> 00:21:43,860
You were in the canteen earlier,
weren't you?

402
00:21:43,860 --> 00:21:44,580
Stay away from me!

403
00:21:44,820 --> 00:21:46,020
Missed me?

404
00:21:46,380 --> 00:21:47,100
You animal!

405
00:21:47,380 --> 00:21:48,700
Missed me, didn't you?

406
00:21:48,700 --> 00:21:49,260
Help!

407
00:21:51,100 --> 00:21:52,380
Let go of me!

408
00:21:53,180 --> 00:21:53,820
Help!

409
00:21:53,820 --> 00:21:54,500
Come on.

410
00:21:55,100 --> 00:21:55,860
Let her go!

411
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:00,060
Gui.

412
00:22:04,380 --> 00:22:05,580
How dare you hit him.

413
00:22:05,780 --> 00:22:06,700
You wretch!

414
00:22:06,860 --> 00:22:07,620
Screw you!

415
00:22:07,860 --> 00:22:08,940
We showed you mercy. You spat on it.

416
00:22:09,100 --> 00:22:10,580
Hit him, I dare you!

417
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:12,060
- You asked for it!
- Take this!

418
00:22:12,180 --> 00:22:12,700
Hit her!

419
00:22:12,940 --> 00:22:13,900
- I'll beat you up!
- You brought this on yourself!

420
00:22:14,060 --> 00:22:15,580
You had it coming.

421
00:22:16,740 --> 00:22:17,420
Hit her hard!

422
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:19,060
Wretch!

423
00:22:20,700 --> 00:22:21,260
You lowly woman!

424
00:22:21,260 --> 00:22:22,060
Stop it!

425
00:22:22,380 --> 00:22:23,820
Please, stop!

426
00:22:23,820 --> 00:22:24,980
I'm begging you!

427
00:22:26,300 --> 00:22:27,140
You earned this!

428
00:22:29,500 --> 00:22:32,540
Please, stop! I beg of you!

429
00:22:33,060 --> 00:22:36,100
I'm begging you. That's enough!

430
00:22:36,660 --> 00:22:38,180
You'll kill her!

431
00:22:38,940 --> 00:22:39,260
You nasty woman!

432
00:22:39,260 --> 00:22:40,500
- Stop!
- Wench!

433
00:22:41,260 --> 00:22:42,860
I'll fight you to the end!

434
00:22:46,620 --> 00:22:47,540
You little punk!

435
00:22:48,060 --> 00:22:49,660
We'll fight you to the bitter end!

436
00:22:51,700 --> 00:22:52,700
Let's take them on!

437
00:22:53,460 --> 00:22:54,100
Hit him!

438
00:22:54,540 --> 00:22:55,260
Smash him!

439
00:22:56,020 --> 00:22:57,460
- You asked for it!
- Take this!

440
00:23:18,220 --> 00:23:19,060
What's going on?

441
00:23:20,420 --> 00:23:21,140
What are you doing?

442
00:23:24,900 --> 00:23:25,580
What the heck are you doing?

443
00:23:26,420 --> 00:23:27,100
Stop it, everyone!

444
00:23:27,980 --> 00:23:28,860
Move!

445
00:23:29,020 --> 00:23:29,620
Out of the way!

446
00:23:35,460 --> 00:23:37,380
This is outrageous.

447
00:23:37,900 --> 00:23:40,140
Starting fights in the factory,

448
00:23:40,140 --> 00:23:41,060
how dare you!

449
00:23:42,060 --> 00:23:43,460
I'll fire every last one of you!

450
00:23:44,060 --> 00:23:45,820
They barged in and started harassing us!

451
00:23:45,980 --> 00:23:46,540
You...

452
00:23:46,780 --> 00:23:49,060
You little vixen!
She was flirting with me earlier!

453
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:49,940
I don't care!

454
00:23:50,500 --> 00:23:51,100
Look

455
00:23:51,260 --> 00:23:52,500
what you've done to them!

456
00:23:53,260 --> 00:23:54,460
This is all your fault!

457
00:23:54,940 --> 00:23:56,820
Workshop 12, you're all

458
00:23:58,260 --> 00:24:00,500
losing half your pay this month!

459
00:24:00,940 --> 00:24:02,140
They started it!

460
00:24:02,260 --> 00:24:03,540
- They kicked it off!
- They caused this!

461
00:24:03,980 --> 00:24:05,380
I decide who gets docked

462
00:24:06,100 --> 00:24:07,780
and by how much.

463
00:24:09,100 --> 00:24:11,300
Anyone who dares to say another word

464
00:24:11,740 --> 00:24:12,860
will be fired on the spot!

465
00:24:13,020 --> 00:24:13,540
Go to sleep!

466
00:24:14,460 --> 00:24:15,620
Work starts on time tomorrow!

467
00:24:16,780 --> 00:24:17,380
Leave!

468
00:24:17,580 --> 00:24:18,380
Wench.

469
00:24:18,900 --> 00:24:20,740
Just you wait!

470
00:24:21,180 --> 00:24:22,060
You'll pay for this!

471
00:24:22,420 --> 00:24:23,220
Let's go.

472
00:24:25,820 --> 00:24:26,900
How could he?

473
00:24:27,460 --> 00:24:28,300
How can he do this to us?

474
00:24:28,420 --> 00:24:29,620
This is outrageous!

475
00:24:29,940 --> 00:24:32,260
Zhong and Lu Agui
are clearly in it together!

476
00:24:32,460 --> 00:24:33,220
Ladies.

477
00:24:34,500 --> 00:24:35,860
You saw what happened.

478
00:24:36,620 --> 00:24:39,700
We gave Lu Agui a real beating.

479
00:24:40,220 --> 00:24:41,100
What does that tell you?

480
00:24:42,180 --> 00:24:44,100
It means if we stand united,

481
00:24:44,740 --> 00:24:46,420
no one can push us around!

482
00:24:47,180 --> 00:24:48,380
Not Lu Agui,

483
00:24:48,700 --> 00:24:49,980
and certainly not Zhong!

484
00:24:51,780 --> 00:24:52,380
Exactly.

485
00:24:52,820 --> 00:24:54,420
But we can't just beat Zhong up

486
00:24:54,540 --> 00:24:55,860
to stop him from docking our pay.

487
00:24:55,860 --> 00:24:56,740
No need to fight.

488
00:24:57,580 --> 00:24:58,500
We go on strike.

489
00:24:58,700 --> 00:24:59,300
Strike?

490
00:24:59,620 --> 00:25:00,420
- Strike?
-Strike?

491
00:25:00,420 --> 00:25:02,060
Yes. Starting tomorrow,

492
00:25:02,460 --> 00:25:03,860
none of us is showing up for work.

493
00:25:04,220 --> 00:25:05,580
But if we don't work,

494
00:25:05,580 --> 00:25:06,740
we won't get paid.

495
00:25:06,980 --> 00:25:09,380
And they might beat us for it.

496
00:25:09,380 --> 00:25:10,380
We are on strike

497
00:25:11,140 --> 00:25:13,020
to fight for the right to not be beaten,

498
00:25:13,780 --> 00:25:16,540
for more wages,

499
00:25:16,940 --> 00:25:18,100
better food,

500
00:25:18,380 --> 00:25:19,660
and a safer workshop.

501
00:25:20,340 --> 00:25:21,780
The boss won't agree, will he?

502
00:25:22,060 --> 00:25:23,620
He will fire us.

503
00:25:24,220 --> 00:25:26,380
Then we won't have a job,

504
00:25:26,380 --> 00:25:27,740
and life will be even worse!

505
00:25:28,060 --> 00:25:28,820
Trust me.

506
00:25:29,340 --> 00:25:30,780
He won't dare to fire us.

507
00:25:31,260 --> 00:25:32,020
Why?

508
00:25:32,500 --> 00:25:36,020
They have an urgent order
to finish right now.

509
00:25:36,380 --> 00:25:37,980
If they can't deliver the goods on time,

510
00:25:37,980 --> 00:25:39,140
they will have to pay a penalty.

511
00:25:39,780 --> 00:25:41,580
If they fire us at this time,

512
00:25:41,980 --> 00:25:43,460
they won't be able
to find skilled workers.

513
00:25:43,820 --> 00:25:45,380
The deadline cannot be delayed.

514
00:25:46,140 --> 00:25:46,700
That's right.

515
00:25:47,060 --> 00:25:48,140
Training a skilled worker

516
00:25:48,140 --> 00:25:49,380
will take at least a week.

517
00:25:50,140 --> 00:25:51,180
So at this moment,

518
00:25:51,180 --> 00:25:52,380
they won't fire us.

519
00:25:53,580 --> 00:25:54,780
As long as we persevere,

520
00:25:55,140 --> 00:25:56,900
they will agree to our terms.

521
00:25:57,220 --> 00:25:58,540
But the premise is,

522
00:25:58,980 --> 00:26:00,420
we must be united

523
00:26:00,740 --> 00:26:01,980
and hold out until the end.

524
00:26:02,620 --> 00:26:03,900
Let's follow Zhu Sha's lead.

525
00:26:04,460 --> 00:26:05,460
A while back,

526
00:26:05,900 --> 00:26:07,340
the workers at the First, Second,

527
00:26:07,380 --> 00:26:08,900
and Third Cotton Mills

528
00:26:09,220 --> 00:26:11,700
went on strike for higher wages.

529
00:26:11,940 --> 00:26:13,740
They held out for 13 days,

530
00:26:14,020 --> 00:26:16,580
and in the end, the factories
agreed to their demands.

531
00:26:17,180 --> 00:26:18,780
So we can follow their example.

532
00:26:18,980 --> 00:26:20,220
Now is the perfect time

533
00:26:20,740 --> 00:26:21,740
to go on strike.

534
00:26:24,020 --> 00:26:24,700
Zhu Sha,

535
00:26:25,140 --> 00:26:26,260
I'm joining the strike.

536
00:26:26,620 --> 00:26:27,100
OK.

537
00:26:27,180 --> 00:26:28,340
I never want to be bullied

538
00:26:28,340 --> 00:26:29,700
by that scoundrel Lu Agui again.

539
00:26:29,820 --> 00:26:30,500
I'm in too!

540
00:26:30,660 --> 00:26:31,420
Me too!

541
00:26:31,540 --> 00:26:33,460
- Add me to the list.
- Count me in.

542
00:26:33,580 --> 00:26:36,700
- I'm in too!
- I'll join as well!

543
00:26:36,860 --> 00:26:37,540
Very well.

544
00:26:42,480 --> 00:26:46,040
[Shanghai Baoxing Cotton Mill]

545
00:27:01,300 --> 00:27:03,420
These women want to
play games with me, huh?

546
00:27:03,900 --> 00:27:04,380
Let's go!

547
00:27:11,580 --> 00:27:12,220
Where is everyone?

548
00:27:12,980 --> 00:27:14,020
Are you all dead?

549
00:27:19,180 --> 00:27:20,060
What are you all doing?

550
00:27:21,100 --> 00:27:22,220
Get back to work!

551
00:27:23,420 --> 00:27:25,740
Mr. Zhong, starting today,

552
00:27:26,460 --> 00:27:29,180
all 1056 female workers
of Baoxing Cotton Mill

553
00:27:29,180 --> 00:27:30,300
are officially on strike.

554
00:27:30,820 --> 00:27:32,260
I am the representative.

555
00:27:32,900 --> 00:27:35,100
Now I will state our terms
for returning to work.

556
00:27:36,780 --> 00:27:38,380
You're trying
to start a rebellion, aren't you?

557
00:27:38,900 --> 00:27:39,420
First,

558
00:27:40,380 --> 00:27:42,140
retract your punishment from last night.

559
00:27:42,620 --> 00:27:45,020
No wages are to be deducted
from any female worker.

560
00:27:45,260 --> 00:27:45,860
Second,

561
00:27:46,380 --> 00:27:50,180
fire the three troublemakers,

562
00:27:50,340 --> 00:27:51,700
Lu Agui, Jiang Dachang, and Mao Wangcai.

563
00:27:52,100 --> 00:27:52,780
Third,

564
00:27:52,940 --> 00:27:54,620
the working hours each day

565
00:27:54,900 --> 00:27:56,540
must not exceed 12 hours.

566
00:27:56,660 --> 00:27:58,620
You can't just add on extra hours.

567
00:27:59,260 --> 00:27:59,940
Fourth,

568
00:28:00,460 --> 00:28:01,780
no more physical
or verbal abuse of female workers.

569
00:28:02,020 --> 00:28:02,900
Especially you.

570
00:28:02,900 --> 00:28:03,660
Bullshit!

571
00:28:03,980 --> 00:28:05,820
Who are you to be making demands?

572
00:28:06,060 --> 00:28:07,420
